                {
                    "file": "src/post_code.cpp",
                    "line": 108,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Patrick Williams",
                        "email": "patrick@stwcx.xyz",
                        "username": "williamspatrick"
                    },
                    "message": "Do you want an else branch here to defer the timer for some period of time?  Is that even possible?"
                },
                {
                    "file": "src/post_code.cpp",
                    "line": 108,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "DelphineCCChiu",
                        "email": "Delphine_CC_Chiu@wiwynn.com",
                        "username": "DelphineCCChiu"
                    },
                    "message": "We will add an else branch and do some tests"
                },
                {
                    "file": "src/post_code.cpp",
                    "line": 108,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "DelphineCCChiu",
                        "email": "Delphine_CC_Chiu@wiwynn.com",
                        "username": "DelphineCCChiu"
                    },
                    "message": "Hi Patrick,\n\nIf we add a branch to defer the timer, the timer is not set as one second that we want."
                },
                {
                    "file": "src/post_code.cpp",
                    "line": 108,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Zhikui Ren",
                        "email": "zhikui.ren@intel.com",
                        "username": "ZhikuiRen"
                    },
                    "message": "You can use the pattern here https://github.com/openbmc/dbus-sensors/blob/master/src/ADCSensorMain.cpp#L325\n\nwhere a new post code update would cancel existing timer and restart a new one. So if file will be written if there is no new post code for one second"
                },
                {
                    "file": "src/post_code.cpp",
                    "line": 111,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Patrick Williams",
                        "email": "patrick@stwcx.xyz",
                        "username": "williamspatrick"
                    },
                    "message": "I'm really surprised that it has to be this verbose.  Can we just do `1s` and let the function arguments automatically do the appropriate conversion?  Does that not work for some reason?  If it doesn't, we should probably improve whatever library that class is coming from."
                },
                {
                    "file": "src/post_code.cpp",
                    "line": 111,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Kuiying Wang",
                        "email": "wangkuiying.wky@alibaba-inc.com",
                        "username": "kuiyingw"
                    },
                    "message": "Two points here:\n1. It is not good to hardcode\n2. I don't think 1s is a reasonable interval, because here is saving into the file, but not memory update."
                },
                {
                    "file": "src/post_code.cpp",
                    "line": 111,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Kuiying Wang",
                        "email": "wangkuiying.wky@alibaba-inc.com",
                        "username": "kuiyingw"
                    },
                    "message": "Note: I suggest to monitor the memory usage to trigger saving to file, but not the timer interval"
                },
                {
                    "file": "src/post_code.cpp",
                    "line": 111,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "DelphineCCChiu",
                        "email": "Delphine_CC_Chiu@wiwynn.com",
                        "username": "DelphineCCChiu"
                    },
                    "message": "We will clean the code and see that it could be built successfully."
                },
                {
                    "file": "src/post_code.cpp",
                    "line": 111,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "DelphineCCChiu",
                        "email": "Delphine_CC_Chiu@wiwynn.com",
                        "username": "DelphineCCChiu"
                    },
                    "message": "The concept is that if BMC frequently opens and closes post code file, there will be more and more dbus-brokers in BMC,\n\nIn that case, the out-of-memory(OOM) issue may happen.\n\nSo if BMC writes post codes into file one time per second, the OOM issue could be avoided."
                },
                {
                    "file": "src/post_code.cpp",
                    "line": 111,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "DelphineCCChiu",
                        "email": "Delphine_CC_Chiu@wiwynn.com",
                        "username": "DelphineCCChiu"
                    },
                    "message": "The concept is that if BMC frequently opens and closes post code file, there will be more and more dbus-brokers in BMC,\n\nIn that case, the out-of-memory(OOM) issue may happen.\n\nSo if BMC writes post codes into file one time per second, the OOM issue could be avoided."
                },
                {
                    "file": "src/post_code.cpp",
                    "line": 111,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Kuiying Wang",
                        "email": "wangkuiying.wky@alibaba-inc.com",
                        "username": "kuiyingw"
                    },
                    "message": "I mean the memory used rate just like before the OOM, but not open post code file."
                },
                {
                    "file": "src/post_code.cpp",
                    "line": 111,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Zhikui Ren",
                        "email": "zhikui.ren@intel.com",
                        "username": "ZhikuiRen"
                    },
                    "message": "The OOM was not because of post code file size. OOM can happen when new post code is coming in a faster rate than an update cycle: dbus update and serialize the new code into the file. Using a timer to only save the file when there is a gap in the post code can prevent this to happen."
                },
                {
                    "file": "src/post_code.cpp",
                    "line": 111,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "DelphineCCChiu",
                        "email": "Delphine_CC_Chiu@wiwynn.com",
                        "username": "DelphineCCChiu"
                    },
                    "message": "We have simplified the code in PS5."
                }
